Package Gui_View.PopUpWindows

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    CancelGame
    CancelGame create a Pop-Up that is displayed when the user clicks on the red "Exit-Button" of the window: this Pop-Up is displayed in every Scene of the Game and does only ask if the user is sure if he is sure to close the game
    ConnectionFailed
    ConnectionFailed creates a PopUp that informs the user that it was not possible to establish a connection with the remote partner and lets him choose whether he wants to go back to the Main Menu oder Exit the Game
    ConnectionLost
    ConnectionLost creates a PopUp that informs the user that the connection to the remote partner was lost and lets him choose whether he wants to go back to the Main Menu oder Exit the Game
    noMatchingSavedGame
    noMatchingSavedGame informs the user that he does not have the saved game the host wants to load -> gives possibility to go back to Main Menu or Exit the Game
    SaveRequest
    SaveRequest creates Pop-Up with two Scenes: 1. when remote Player in MP wants to save, the user has to enter a name for the gamefile. 2. success: when successfully saved, this scene is shown.
    unexpectedMessageFromRemote
    unexpectedMessageFromRemote informs the user that there was an unexpected message send by the remote -> failure of remote programm -> user can go back to Main Menu or Exit the Game
    WinLose
    WinLose creates PopUps that inform the user whether he has won or lost the game these let him also decide whether he wants to head back to the Main Menu or to completely close the game
